<h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">If set to TRUE, it enables the threshold/reset override
feature for monitor policies in the monitor agent.<o:p></o:p></p>

<h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Obtain the threshold values to be overridden from
[eaagt.thresholds] namespace.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Eg value for the above config variable is as follows:<br><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">ovconfchg -ns eaagt.thresholds -set threshold1
Monitor1/threshold1/10:7</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>The value before the first “/” separator is policy name. In
the above example “Monitor1” is the policy name.</li><li>The value 10 indicates the threshold value.</li><li>The value 7 indicates reset value.</li></ul><o:p></o:p><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Post obtaining the above values threshold overriding is done
in the following manner:<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>For each deployed monitor policies</li><li>For each threshold override configuration specified if
policy name matches then below flow of actions happen</li><li>For each conditions in the policy if the description matches
then </li><li>Threshold value in the policy is overwritten in memory</li><li>Reset value in the policy is overwritten in memory.</li><li>Also, the following value is also altered if the threshold
value is not the same as reset value</li><li>If message generation is for BELOW_THRESHOLD it is altered
as BELOW_RESET</li><li>Similar flow is also performed for the case with advanced
monitor policies</li><li>The threshold value overriding is performed during fresh
start of subagent process and during reconfig scenarios</li></ul><div><h2>OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </h2><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

