<h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT config variable is used
to set maximum time opcmona process can wait to get SNMP MIB data.<o:p></o:p></p>

<h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">When opcmona process monitors SNMP MIB Measurement threshold
policy, it tries to fetch the MIB data every interval and checks for the threshold
and performs the necessary action.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Opcmona process fetches the MIB data by opening snmp session
and request snmp Query and get the data and close the snmp session.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">By default, opcmona wait for 2 second to get the MIB data and
close the session.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Possible scenarios where&nbsp;OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT&nbsp;variable could be used:</b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">Sometime opcmona need to get the MIB data from Remote node
as well. During this scenario, there is a possibility of delay in receiving the
MIB data from the remote node and opcmona policy fails with the below error in
System.txt.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>Initialization of MIB source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-726)</li><li>Collect data from SNMP source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-719)</li><li>Can't issue an SNMP GET request for monitor.</li></ul><o:p></o:p><p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">To overcome this situation we can use
OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT config variable to increase the number of
second the snmp session can be opened to get the MIB data from the remote node.</p><h2>OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_RETRIES</h2><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
