</tbody></table><h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_RETRIES config variable is used
to set Maximum number of retries to fetch SNMP MIB.<o:p></o:p></p><h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">When opcmona process monitors SNMP MIB Measurement threshold
policy, it try to fetch the MIB data every interval and check for the threshold
and perform necessary action.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Opcmona process fetch the MIB data by opening snmp session
and request Snmp Query and get the data and close the snmp session.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Possible Scenarios where OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_RETRIES
variable could be used:</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Sometime opcmona need to get the MIB data from Remote node
as well. During this scenario there is possibility of delay in receiving the
MIB data from the remote node and opcmona policy fails with the below error in
System.txt.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><ul><li>Initialization of MIB source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-726)</li><li>Collect data from SNMP source SNMPsource failed. (OpC30-719)</li><li>Can't issue an SNMP GET request for monitor</li></ul><o:p></o:p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">























</p><p class="MsoNormal">To overcome the situation we can use
OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_RETRIES config variable to increase the number of
Retries to fetch the MIB data after every OPC_OPCMON_NETSNMP_SESSION_TIMEOUT
seconds.<o:p></o:p></p><h2>OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE</h2><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
