</tbody></table><h3><b>Short Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE config variable is used to set stack
size of opcmona threads. Default value for this config variable is Linux (
524288),AIX( 262144),SOLARIS and HPUX( 5242880)<o:p></o:p></p><h3><b>Long Description</b></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Opcmona process creates each thread per opcmona policy
deployed in the node.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">When new thread is getting created, thread allocate memory
space to hold the information of the program variables in the memory space
called “Stack Memory Region”.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">This stack memory gets freed once the thread is stopped.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Possible Scenarios where&nbsp;
OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE variable could be used:</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">There can be a situation that when opmona policy is needed
more memory to store the program variable but stack memory allocated to the
thread is less. Opcmona process abort with the “Stack Overflow” error. <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">



















</p><p class="MsoNormal">To avoid the opcmona abort we can use the config variable to
increase the thread stack size. Maximum value that can be set to the
OPC_THREAD_STACK_SIZE is 10 MB.<o:p></o:p></p></div><o:p></o:p><p></p>

